Note: we want to make some implementation on Task
      so we use abstract class instead of an Interface!
      Task is our Template

Note: we have two constructor on Task class (Mosh version)
      one of them is default (with no parameter)
      one of them with AuditTrail parameter
      can share an audit trial obj amongst any different tasks
      even we can use it for developing an interface
      to decouple AuditTrail from Task class later!

Note: by creating an any subTask classes obj (like TransferMoneyTask)                 public Task() {
      Java runtime is going to call the default constructor of task class             this.auditTrail = new AuditTrail();
       (so there we instantiate AuditTrail obj)                                         }

Note: I implement a abstract class with no abstract method!
      Mosh create a abstract class with a abstract method!

important note: if main class has access to doExecute()
                we can do task without AuditTrial (it's not correct)
                we can not make doExecute() private on subclasses
                (access modifier could not be private on subclasses, but public on parent!)
                we can not make doExecute() private on Task
                (the method can not be inheritance by subclasses)

                solution: use protected access modifier
                          it's like private, but visible to "subclasses"




